main event: A military observation reported a white round object, potentially a satellite, spotted on April 15, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size and intensity of a first magnitude star., It was flying at a high altitude of 70 degrees elevation., The object was traveling at a very high speed., The observation location was in the Pacific, with coordinates around 36.10 N 174.00 W., The conclusion noted insufficient data for evaluation, indicating it may be a satellite.
